GOVERNMENT ORDER NUMBER: MOVISA-1024 / Q.No. 110/2024 AASTA-3
3rd Floor, Construction Building, 25 Marzban Street,
Fort, Mantralaya, Mumbai-01
Date: 9th October, 2024
The Government Court:

Pursuant to the provisions of the Maharashtra Regulation of Transfer of Government Employees and Prevention of Delay in discharge of Government Duties in the interest of Public Service Act, 2005, the Government, on the recommendation of the Civil Services Board and with the approval of the authorities competent to make the transfer and the provisions of Sections 4 (4) and 4 (5) of the said Act, is issuing orders for the transfer of Shri Limbaji Bargire, Group-A Cadre, Maharashtra Development Service, Group Development Officer, Panchayat Samiti, Kalamnuri, G. Hingoli on administrative grounds. The officer concerned is being posted in the position indicated in column no. 3 in front of his name.

02. The said order comes into immediate effect and the officer concerned shall join the post indicated in the order of posting forthwith. Also, the officers concerned should not go on unauthorised leave. The attention of the concerned authorities is being drawn to the Government Circular No: CDR 1082/2567/28 XI, dated 30.08.1982 of the General Administration Department. They should note that if the officers concerned submit any form of application for change of posting / cancellation of appointment, they will be liable for disciplinary action as per the instructions in the said Government Circular.
The concerned Divisional Commissioner / CEO, Zilla Parishad should ask the officer posted to join immediately in place of his / her appointment.

The officer concerned shall appear at the place of the new appointment and inform the Government of the date of assumption of office. If the officer concerned fails to join the post established within the prescribed time, the concerned CEO, Zila Parishad shall submit a proposal to the Government for disciplinary action against the said officer through the Divisional Commissioners.
